CONTENT: Dear Rishob,  I'm an engineering recruiter at Goldman Sachs where I support a couple of different teams & divisions. I'm interested in digging a bit deeper into your background to better understand your skill set and aspirations moving forward to see what potential opportunities we have that may be a good fit. This is an amazing opportunity to help build out and run the automated trading systems and associated research platform of the Systematic Market Making Micro (SMM Micro) group. We are looking for a developer with strong technical skills to contribute to and support all parts of the system such as latency sensitive trading applications, research tools and GUI code. With this said, we're looking for top-tier Software Engineers to join the team and help lead new and existing projects. After viewing your profile, I feel your experience aligns very well with someone we think could bring a lot to our team/division.  Job Title - Vice President/Associate/Analyst,  Location - Bengaluru, KA Hyderabad, TN  Job Specifics: • 1 - 5 years’ experience developing high-performance software in C++ or Java • A strong desire to produce organised, readable and maintainable software • Effective communicator in both written and verbal mediums  • Proven problem solving ability with critical and creative thinking • Ability to balance multiple, time-sensitive projects while maintaining a longer term, strategic focus  If you're interested in discussing in more detail, feel free to send me an updated resume to Sandhya.Moganti@gs.com and let me know a good time to reach out. Look forward to hearing back! Thank you, Sandhya Moganti Talent Acquisition at Goldman Sachs
